<h2 id="definition">Definition</h2>

<p>Transformation: A function that takes in an input vector and <em>moves</em> it.
Linear: The <em>movement</em> described above is linear if and only if</p>

<ol>
  <li>the origin remains</li>
  <li>lines stay as lines. (In other words, the set of vectors that have the same span do not change after the transformation)</li>
</ol>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">% <![CDATA[
\begin{bmatrix}
i_1 & i_2 \\
j_1 & j_2
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
a & b \\
c & d
\end{bmatrix} %]]></script>
